{"type":"message","id":"da9cf6ad","parentId":"eda206cb","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:06.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent \"哈喽\" which is a casual greeting in Chinese. This seems to be a new message after the previous session where we were configuring the Feishu bot. \n\nLooking at the chat_id, it's \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\" which is the same as before, and the channel is \"feishu\" with account \"kiit\". This seems to be the same user.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at the system message, the channel is \"feishu[kiit]\" not \"feishu[default]\". This might indicate that the user now has a different Feishu bot account active (kiit) compared to the previous session.\n\nThe user is just saying hi casually. I should respond in a friendly way and ask how the bot configuration went (if they restarted the gateway and tested it).\n\nSince this appears to be the same user from before (HALEI), I should greet them warmly and ask about the status of the Feishu bot they were setting up.","thinkingSignature":"0ae4a23d425c6b06dc6714185095a6b3bc433255635ee235a00b09835f0029e3"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 哈喽！昨晚的选品 Bot 配置好了吗？有没有重启网关测试过？发消息给 bot 有响应吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":140,"output":256,"cacheRead":23780,"cacheWrite":36785,"totalTokens":60961,"cost":{"input":0.000042,"output":0.0003072,"cacheRead":0.0014267999999999998,"cacheWrite":0.013794375000000001,"total":0.015570375000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775059495675,"responseId":"061c7528b1c3b205e577da25eb7e93d7"}}
