{"type":"message","id":"cca7bf97","parentId":"cd24c2ce","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:27.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"你是谁\" (who are you). They might not recognize me or might be asking about my identity/role. Looking at the chat_id, it says \"Feishu[kiit]\" which is different from the \"Feishu[default]\" we saw before. \n\nWait - the chat_id is the same \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\" but the channel account is \"kiit\" not \"default\". This might mean that this message is coming through a different Feishu bot account (kiit) than the one we configured earlier.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the user is now talking to me through a DIFFERENT Feishu bot called \"kiit\" (which might be the new app we just configured with cli_a930f78f51399bc6), whereas before they were talking through \"default\".\n\nBut wait, the message content is just \"你是谁\" - the user is asking who I am. This could mean:\n1. They don't recognize me\n2. They're asking about my role/identity\n3. The bot connection might not be working properly and they're testing\n\nSince the channel shows \"kiit\", this might actually be the newly configured bot (tts/选品专家) that we bound to the new Feishu app. So the user might be asking the 选品专家 bot who I am.\n\nActually, thinking about it more - the session context shows I'm running as \"agent=main | host=halei-Surface-Pro-4\" and the channel is \"feishu\" with capabilities=\"none\". This suggests I'm the main agent, not the tts agent.\n\nThe user might be confused about which bot they're talking to, or they're asking about my identity. I should clarify that I'm the main assistant (大管家) and explain what I'm here to help with.\n\nLet me respond in Chinese since the user has been communicating in Chinese.","thinkingSignature":"bc2d3772b500fe9206c918cb97dc07d25b3f292944a5def40c279addb3a8642f"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 我是你的**首席助理大总管** 🎯\n\n昨晚帮你配置了飞书 bot（选品专家 ag